news.title: Capitaland Investment to acquire 40% stake in SC Capital Partners Group for $209.31 million
news.para: CapitaLand's 40% stake acquisition in SCCP, a Singapore-based real estate investment manager, will increase its funds under management (FUM) by S$11 billion.

news.title: Myanmar nationals snap up properties in Thailand
news.para: Thai condominium unit sales to Myanmar nationals in the first nine months of 2024 tripled from the same period last year, according to the Real Estate Information Center (REIC), making them the second-largest group of foreign buyers after those from China.

news.title: Gurugram: Raheja Developers moves NCLAT against insolvency proceedings
news.para: On Tuesday, the Principal Bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) admitted a plea filed by over 40 of its flat allottees of Sector 109, Gurugram-based projects and directed to initiate a Corporate Insolvency Resolution Process (CIRP).

news.title: Bihar mining department realises Rs 18 lakh fine during raids
news.para: A mines and geology department communiqué said that the raids were conducted to prevent illegal mining, transportation and storage of sand, transportation of stone chips and digging of earth and its transportation for commercial use.

news.title: ED arrests two persons in PMLA case linked to illegal sand mining in HP, UP
news.para: The two persons -- Gian Chand and Sanjay Dhiman -- have been taken into custody under the provisions of the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) on Monday, the federal probe agency said in a statement.

news.title: British Land reports higher half-year profit driven by retail park investments
news.para: The British commercial property market is recovering from the post-pandemic freeze, with stabilizing property values and expectations of near-term rate cuts boosting sector optimism.

news.title: US: Single family housing sees decline in October 2024 due to high mortgage rates
news.para: The report from the Commerce Department on Tuesday suggested that residential investment, which includes homebuilding, remained subdued at the start of the fourth quarter after contracting in the last two quarters.

news.title: Kochi metro phase II work delayed due to land acquisition issues
news.para: ​​Revenue authorities have extended the validity of the 11(1) notification for six months, pushing back the issuance of the 19(1) notification for several stations.

news.title: Bengaluru: Residents oppose construction in Jayanthinagar lake buffer zone
news.para: The residents said the construction work began two years ago and came to a halt within a few days.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP urges defaulters to clear tax dues before November 30
news.para: Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP) sources told TOI categorically that defaulters cannot expect any extension of the OTS deadline beyond Nov 30, as there have been multiple extensions already.

news.title: Kolkata civic body launches land reclamation drive to curb encroachments
news.para: KMC has planned to reclaim vast stretches of land both on the outskirts of EM Bypass and in different parts of Kolkata within 144 wards

news.title: Bhubaneswar: Around 116 families receive housing allotments under BDA project
news.para: Housing & urban development minister Krushna Chandra Mahapatra, who also chairs the Bhubaneswar Development Authority (BDA), distributed the letters to beneficiaries from three different housing projects

news.title: Gurugram civic body imposes Rs 3.4 lakh fines for GRAP violations
news.para: Of this, Rs 1.4 lakh (41% of the penalty amount) was issued for carrying out construction activities, a major GRAP violation, especially when the air quality is consistently deteriorating.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 53-acre land in Joka, Kolkata
news.para: The proposed project is estimated to have a development potential of about 1.3 million sq ft of saleable area comprising primarily residential plotted development with an estimated revenue potential of Rs 500 crore.

news.title: Self-survey, facial recognition to be used in new survey for PMAY-G second phase: Sources
news.para: According to a source from the Rural Development Ministry, for the first time, facial recognition technology will be used for both surveyors and those surveyed to maintain transparency.

news.title: Authority starts survey of land to be acquired for new Noida
news.para: Noida CEO Lokesh M said, "We inspected the proposed land in the Sikandrabad area of Bulandshahr. We also inspected the land in Jokhabad village for a temporary office of the Noida Authority, which will supervise the land acquisition and development works in the area.

news.title: Telangana RERA imposes 18 lakh penalty on Sterling Homes for delays
news.para: The project, located in Mallampet Village of Medchal-Malkajgiri district, was originally scheduled for completion by July 1, 2023, with a grace period extending to Dec 2023

news.title: Telangana RERA orders Aliens Developers to complete project
news.para: The Authority also ordered the developer to pay interest at the rate of 10.95% per annum from Dec 2017 to the date of possession, excluding the Covid-19 waiver period, for delays in delivering the flat.

news.title: NCLT directs initiation of insolvency proceedings against Raheja Developers
news.para: The National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) has initiated insolvency proceedings against Raheja Developers following a petition by flat buyers in the Gurgaon-based Shilas project. The NCLT cited "debt due and default" by the company for its failure to deliver units on time despite receiving payments. An Interim Resolution Professional has been appointed as the case proceeds.

news.title: Bombay HC directs civic bodies to link their websites with Maharashtra RERA
news.para: "This integration would enable RERA to conduct real-time verification of commencement and occupation certificates, thereby preventing forgery and protecting consumers' interests in line with the RERA Act's objectives," said Chief Justice Devendra Kumar Upadhyaya and Justice Amit Borkar.
